               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism, 3 items (a-c)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 https://lccn.loc.gov/gf2015026087">
                  <summary>Collection of works on Sufism. Volume not dated; datable to the mid
							fifteenth century. Neat semi-calligraphic rounded naskh becoming a
							little compressed later, eventually switching to an archaic scribal
							nastaʿlīq (after f. 100), by multiple hands. Annotations and corrections
							in margins by later hands. Stamped foliation. Lacking original binding.
							Binding, red half leather IOL covers, stamp dated 14 May 1916. Folios
							rebound; cropped, water stained, wormholes, gauze overlay on folios at
							either end. </summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_96-item1" n="a">
                     <locus from="1v" to="126v">ff. 1v-126v </locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>
                           <idno>Delhi Persian 96(a)</idno>
                        Treatise on litany, invocations, and remembrances for meditation
									in Sufi ritual by an author identifying himself simply as
									Jaʿfarī, inspired by the author’s master, 
									<persName key="viaf_90062645" role="oth" change="#role-assignment">Hamadhānī, `Alī ibn Muhammad 1314-1385</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Defective at end. </p>
                        <p>Not dated on end.</p>
                        <p>Illuminated sarlawḥ on the opening folio, with gilt and blue
									rulings limited to folios 1v-2r. </p>
                        <p>The text on folio 117r (with the verso left blank) is repeated on
									folio 118r. </p>
                     </note>
                     <author key="person_f6269">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Jaʿfarī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">جعفرى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_11469">Awrād-i fatḥīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_11469">اوراد فتحيّه</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_96-item2" n="b">
                     <locus from="127r" to="127v">f. 127 </locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>
                           <idno>Delhi Persian 96(b) </idno>
                        Excerpt possibly from a historical work mentioning the emergence
									of an unidentified disease among Romans. This is followed by a
									ghazal on the appearance of a star identified as the Sitārah-i
									Shukr Yildūz by an unnamed author. This is followed by
									instructions on entering a mosque. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. </p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_96-item3" n="c">
                     <locus from="128r" to="128r">f. 128 </locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>
                           <idno>Delhi Persian 96(c) </idno>. Another leaf, possibly the
									concluding folio, from the item Delhi Persian 96 a, in the same
									hand. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work does not appear to flow from folio 126v. </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. </p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
